''[[Famitsu]]'' appreciated the game's graphics and animations, and called the characters "cute".<ref name="famitsu">{{cite magazine |url=http://www.famitsu.com/cominy/?m=pc&a=page_h_title&title_id=18356 |title=クレオパトラの魔宝 [ファミコン] |magazine=[[Famitsu]] |access-date=25 July 2015 |language=Japanese |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725120112/http://www.famitsu.com/cominy/?m=pc&a=page_h_title&title_id=18356 |archive-date=25 July 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> ''ITmedia Gamez'' also complimented the game's animations, though felt that too much of the disk's capacity was devoted to these animations at the cost of game length. However, the reviewer thought it was not a bad game, even though it was short, and compared it favorably to ''[[The Warlock of Firetop Mountain]]'', an [[adventure gamebook]].<ref name="itmedia"/>

